INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('781', '', '1', '1. Do the following:', '30', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('782', '', '2', '  a. Tour your community and list the different building types you see. Try to identify buildings that can be associated with a specific period of history or style of architecture. Make a sketch of the building you most admire.', '30', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('783', '', '3', '  b. Select an architectural achievement that has had a major impact on society. Using resources such as the Internet (with your parent\'s permission), books, and magazines, find out how this achievement has influenced the world today. Tell your counselor what you learned.', '30', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('784', '', '4', '2. In the Outdoor Code, a Scout pledges to be conservation-minded. Discuss the following with your counselor:', '30', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('785', '', '5', '  a. The term sustainable architecture. Identify three features typical of green buildings.', '30', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('786', '', '6', '  b. The difference between renewable building materials and recycled building materials, and how each can be used in construction.', '30', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('787', '', '7', '  c. The relationship of architecture with its surrounding environment and the community.', '30', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('788', '', '8', '  d. How entire buildings can be reused rather than torn down when they no longer serve their original purpose.', '30', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('789', '', '9', '3. Do ONE of the following:', '30', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('790', '', '10', '  a. With your parent\'s and counselor\'s permission and approval, arrange to meet with an architect. Ask to see the scale model of a building and the drawings that a builder would use to construct this building. Discuss why the different building materials were selected. Look at the details in the drawings and the scale model to see how the materials and components are attached to each other during construction.', '30', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('791', '', '11', '  b. With your parent\'s and counselor\'s permission and approval, arrange to meet with an architect at a construction site. Ask the architect to bring drawings that the builder uses to construct the building. While at the site, discuss why the different building materials being used were selected. Discuss how the different building materials and components are attached to each other during construction.\n    Note: To visit a construction site will require advance planning. You will need permission from your parents, counselor, the architect, and the construction site manager. A construction site is a very dangerous place. While there, you will need to closely follow the site manager\'s directions and comply with all the safety procedures, including wearing a hard hat protective eyewear, and proper footwear.', '30', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('792', '', '12', '  c. Interview someone who might be your client (such as a prospective homeowner or business owner) if you were an architect. Find out what your client\'s requirements would be for designing a new home or business building. Write a short program including a list of requirements for the project, the functions of the building and site, hoe the functions relate to one another, and the goals of the project.', '30', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('793', '', '13', '4. Measure a room such as one where you live or where your troop meets. Make an accurately scaled drawing of the room\'s floor plan showing walls, doors, closets, windows, and any built-in furniture or cabinets. Neatly label your drawing with the following: your name, the date, what room you drew, and the scale of the drawing. (Drawing scale: 1/4 inch = 1 foot)', '30', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('794', '', '14', '5. Find out about three career opportunities in architecture. Pick one and find out the education, training, and experience required for this profession. Discuss this with your counselor, and explain why this profession might interest you.', '30', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('795', '', '1', '1. Tell a story with a picture or pictures or using a 3-D rendering.', '31', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('796', '', '2', '2. Do ONE of the following.', '31', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('797', '', '3', '  a. Design something useful. Make a sketch or model of your design and get your counselor\'s approval before you proceed. Then create a promotional piece for the item using a picture or pictures.', '31', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('798', '', '4', '  b. Design a logo. Share your design with your counselor and explain the significance of your logo. Then, with your parent\'s permission and your counselor\'s approval, put your logo on Scout equipment, furniture, ceramics, or fabric.', '31', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('799', '', '5', '3. Render a subject of your choice in FOUR of these ways:', '31', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('800', '', '6', '  a. Pen and ink,', '31', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('801', '', '7', '  b. Watercolors,', '31', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('802', '', '8', '  c. Pencil, ', '31', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('803', '', '9', '  d. Pastels,', '31', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('804', '', '10', '  e. Oil paints,', '31', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('805', '', '11', '  f. Tempera,', '31', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('806', '', '12', '  g. Acrylics,', '31', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('807', '', '13', '  h. Charcoal,', '31', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('808', '', '14', '  i. Computer drawing or painting.', '31', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('809', '', '15', '4. With your parent\'s permission and your counselor\'s approval, visit a museum, art exhibit, art gallery, artists\' co-op, or artist\'s workshop. Find out about the art displayed or created there. Discuss what you learn with your counselor.', '31', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('810', '', '16', '5. Find out about three career opportunities in art. Pick one and find out the education, training, and experience required for this profession. Discuss this with your counselor, and explain why this profession might interest you.', '31', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('811', '', '2', '  a. Describe the proper clothing and other precautions for safely making observations at night and in cold weather.', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('812', '', '5', '2. Explain what light pollution is and how it and air pollution affect astronomy. ', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('813', '', '6', '3. With the aid of diagrams (or real telescopes if available), do each of the following: ', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('814', '', '7', '  a. Explain why binoculars and telescopes are important astronomical tools. Demonstrate or explain how these tools are used.', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('815', '', '8', '  b. Describe the similarities and differences of several types of astronomical telescopes.', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('816', '', '9', '  c. Explain the purposes of at least three instruments used with astronomical telescopes.', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('817', '', '11', '4. Do the following:', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('818', '', '12', '  a. Identify in the sky at least 10 constellations, at least four of which are in the zodiac.', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('819', '', '13', '  b. Identify at least eight conspicuous stars, five of which are of magnitude 1 or brighter. ', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('820', '', '14', '  c. Make two sketches of the Big Dipper. In one sketch, show the Big Dipper\'s orientation in the early evening sky. In another sketch, show its position several hours later. In both sketches, show the North Star and the horizon. Record the date and time each sketch was made.', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('821', '', '15', '  d. Explain what we see when we look at the Milky Way.', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('822', '', '16', '5. Do the following:', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('823', '', '17', '  a. List the names of the five most visible planets. Explain which ones can appear in phases similar to lunar phases and which ones cannot, and explain why.', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('824', '', '18', '  b. Using the Internet (with your parent\'s permission) and other resources, find out when each of the five most visible planets that you identified in requirement 5a will be observable in the evening sky during the next 12 months, then compile this information in the form of a chart or table. Update your chart monthly to show whether each planet will be visible during the early morning or in the evening sky.', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('825', '', '21', '6. Do the following:', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('826', '', '22', '  a. Sketch the face of the moon and indicate at least five seas and five craters. Label these landmarks.', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('827', '', '23', '  b. Sketch the phase and the daily position of the Moon at the same hour and place, for a week. Include landmarks on the horizon such as hills, trees, and buildings. Explain the changes you observe.', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('828', '', '24', '  c. List the factors that keep the Moon in orbit around Earth. ', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('829', '', '25', '  d. With the aid of diagrams, explain the relative positions of the Sun, Earth, and the Moon at the times of lunar and solar eclipses, and at the times of new, first-quarter, full, and last-quarter phases of the Moon.', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('830', '', '26', '7. Do the following: ', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('831', '', '27', '  a. Describe the composition of the Sun, its relationship to other stars, and some effects of its radiation on Earth\'s weather. Define sunspots and describe some of the effects they may have on solar radiation.', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('832', '', '29', '  c. Identify at least one red star, one blue star, and one yellow star (other than the Sun). Explain the meaning of these colors. ', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('833', '', '30', '8. With your counselor\'s approval and guidance, do ONE of the following: ', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('834', '', '31', '  a. Visit a planetarium or astronomical observatory. Submit a written report, a scrapbook, or a video presentation afterward to your counselor that includes the following information:', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('835', '', '32', '    1. Activities occurring there', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('836', '', '33', '    2. Exhibits and displays you saw', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('837', '', '34', '    3. Telescopes and instruments being used ', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('838', '', '35', '    4. Celestial objects you observed. ', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('839', '', '36', '  b. Plan and participate in a three-hour observation session that includes using binoculars or a telescope. List the celestial objects you want to observe, and find each on a star chart or in a guidebook. Prepare an observing log or notebook. Show your plan, charts, and log or notebook to your counselor before making your observations. Review your log or notebook with your counselor afterward.', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('840', '', '37', '  c. Plan and host a star party for your Scout troop or other group such as your class at school. Use binoculars or a telescope to show and explain celestial objects to the group. ', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('841', '', '38', '  d. Help an astronomy club in your community hold a star party that is open to the public.', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('842', '', '39', '  e. Personally take a series of photographs or digital images of the movement of the Moon, a planet, an asteroid or meteoroid, or a comet. In your visual display, label each image and include the date and time it was taken. Show all positions on a star chart or map. Show your display at school or at a troop meeting. Explain the changes you observed.', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('843', '', '40', '9. List at least three different career opportunities in astronomy. Pick the one you in which are most interested and explain how to prepare for such a career. Discuss with your counselor what courses might be useful for such a career.', '32', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('844', '', '1', '1. Show that you know first aid for injuries or illnesses that could occur while participating in athletic events, including sprains, strains, contusions, abrasions, blisters, dehydration, and heat reactions.', '33', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('845', '', '2', '2. Explain the following:', '33', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('846', '', '3', '  a. The importance of the physical exam', '33', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('847', '', '4', '  b. The importance of maintaining good health habits, especially during training - and how the use of tobacco products, alcohol, and other harmful substances can negatively affect your health and performance in athletic activities.', '33', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('848', '', '5', '  c. The importance of maintaining a healthy diet.', '33', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('849', '', '6', '3. Select an athletic activity to participate in for one season (or four months). Then do the following:', '33', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('850', '', '7', '  a. With guidance from your counselor, establish a personal training program suited to the activity you have chosen.', '33', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('851', '', '8', '  b. Organize a chart for this activity and monitor your progress during this time.', '33', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('852', '', '9', '  c. Explain to your counselor the equipment necessary to participate in this activity, and the appropriate clothing for the season and the locale.', '33', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('853', '', '10', '  d. At the end of the season, discuss with your counselor the progress you have made during training and competition and how your development has affected you mentally and physically.', '33', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('854', '', '11', '4. Do the following:', '33', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('855', '', '12', '  a. Give the rules for two athletic activities, one of which is the activity you chose for requirement 3.', '33', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('856', '', '13', '  b. Discuss the importance of warming up and cooling down.', '33', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('857', '', '14', '  c. Explain to your counselor what an amateur athlete is and the differences between an amateur and a professional athlete. ', '33', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('858', '', '15', '  d. Discuss the traits and importance of good sportsmanship. Tell what role sportsmanship plays in both individual and group athletic activities.', '33', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('859', '', '16', '5. Complete the activities in FOUR of the following groups and show improvement over a three-month period.', '33', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('860', '', '17', '  Group 1: Sprinting\n  a. 100-meter dash\n  b. 200-meter dash', '33', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('861', '', '18', '  Group 2: Long-Distance Running \n  a. 3k run \n  b. 5k run', '33', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('862', '', '19', '  Group 3: Long Jump OR High Jump \n  a. Running long jump OR running high jump (best of three tries) \n  b. Standing long jump OR standing high jump (best of three tries)', '33', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('863', '', '21', '  Group 5: Pull-Ups AND Push-Ups \n  a. Pull-ups in two minutes \n  b. Push-ups in two minutes', '33', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('864', '', '22', '  Group 6: Baseball Throw \n  a. Baseball throw for accuracy, 10 throws \n  b. Baseball throw for distance, five throws (total distance)', '33', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('865', '', '23', '  Group 7: Basketball Shooting \n  a. Basketball shot for accuracy, 10 free-throw shots \n  b. Basketball throw for skill and agility, the following shots as shown on the diagram\n    1. Left-side layup \n    2. Right-side layup \n    3. Left side of hoop, along the key line \n    4. Right side of hoop, along the key line \n    5. Where key line and free-throw line meet, left side \n    6. Where key line and free-throw line meet, right side \n    7. Top of the key \n    8. Anywhere along the three-point line.', '33', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('866', '', '24', '  Group 8: Football Kick OR Soccer Kick \n  a. Goals from the 10-yard line, eight kicks \n  b. Football kick or soccer kick for distance, five kicks (total distance)', '33', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('867', '', '25', '  Group 9: Weight Training \n  a. Chest/bench press, two sets of 15 repetitions each \n  b. Leg curls, two sets of 15 repetitions each', '33', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('868', '', '26', '6. Do the following', '33', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('869', '', '27', '  a. Prepare plans for conducting a sports meet or field day that includes 10activities, at least five of which must come from the groups mentioned in requirement 5. Outline the duties of each official needed and list the equipment the meet will require.', '33', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('870', '', '28', '  b. With your parent\'s and counselor\'s approval, serve as an official or volunteer at a sports meet to observe officials in action. Tell your counselor about your responsibilities at the meet and discuss what you learned.', '33', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('871', '', '4', '  b. Discuss with your counselor the safety equipment, tools, and clothing used while checking or repairing a motor vehicle. Use this equipment, tools, and/or clothing (when needed or called for) in meeting the requirements for this merit badge.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('872', '', '5', '2. General Maintenance, Safety, and Registration Do the following:', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('873', '', '6', '  a. Review the maintenance chart in the owner\'s manual. Explain the requirements and time limits.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('874', '', '7', '  b. Demonstrate how to check the following:', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('875', '', '8', '    1. Brake Fluid', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('876', '', '9', '    2. Engine Oil', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('877', '', '10', '    3. Coolant', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('878', '', '11', '    4. Power steering fluid', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('879', '', '12', '    5. Windshield washer fluid', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('880', '', '13', '    6. Transmission fluid', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('881', '', '14', '    7. Battery fluid (if possible) and condition of the battery terminals ', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('882', '', '15', '  c. Locate the fuse boxes; determine the size of fuses. Demonstrate the proper replacement of burned-out fuses.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('883', '', '16', '  d. Demonstrate how to check the condition and tension of belts and hoses.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('884', '', '17', '  e. Check the lighting in the vehicle, including instrument, warning, and exterior bulbs.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('885', '', '18', '  f. Locate and check the air filter.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('886', '', '19', '  g. Explain the purpose, importance, and limitations of safety belts and passive restraints.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('887', '', '20', '  h. Find out the requirements for the state inspection in your state, including how often a vehicle needs to be inspected.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('888', '', '21', '  i. Explain the importance of registering a vehicle and find out the annual registration fee for renewing your family car\'s registration. ', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('889', '', '22', '3. Dashboard. Do the following:', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('890', '', '23', '  a. Explain the function of the fuel gauge, speedometer, tachometer, oil pressure, and engine temperature gauge. Point out each one on the instrument cluster.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('891', '', '24', '  b. Explain the symbols that light up on the dashboard and the difference between the yellow and red symbols. Explain each of the indicators on the dashboard, using the owner\'s manual, if necessary. ', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('892', '', '25', '4. Tires. Do the following:', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('893', '', '26', '  a. Explain the difference between tire manufacturer\'s and vehicle manufacturer\'s specifications and show where to find them.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('894', '', '27', '  b. Demonstrate how to check pressure and properly inflate a tire. Check the spare tire and make sure it is ready for use.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('895', '', '28', '  c. Explain why wheel alignment is important to the life of a tire. Explain camber, caster, and toe-in adjustments on wheel alignment.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('896', '', '29', '  d. Explain the purpose of the lateral-wear bar indicator.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('897', '', '30', '  e. Explain how to dispose of old tires in accordance with local laws and regulations.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('898', '', '31', '5. Engine. Do the following:', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('899', '', '32', '  a. Explain how an internal combustion engine operates. Tell the differences between gasoline and diesel engines. Explain how a gasoline-electric hybrid vehicle is powered.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('900', '', '33', '  b. Discuss the purpose of engine oil. Explain the API service code, the SAE number, and the viscosity rating.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('901', '', '34', '  c. Explain where to find the recommended oil type and the amount of oil to be used in the vehicle\'s engine.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('902', '', '35', '6. Cooling system. Do the following:', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('903', '', '36', '  a. Explain the need for coolant in the cooling system.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('904', '', '37', '  b. Explain how to flush and change the engine coolant in the vehicle , and how to properly dispose of the used coolant.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('905', '', '38', '7. Fuel system. Do the following:', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('906', '', '39', '  a. Explain how the air and fuel systems work together and why it is necessary to have an air filter and fuel filter.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('907', '', '40', '  b. Explain how a how a fuel injection system works and how an on-board computer works with the fuel injection system.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('908', '', '41', '8. Ignition and electrical systems. Do the following:', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('909', '', '42', '  a. Diagram and explain the parts of the electrical system.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('910', '', '43', '  b. Explain the cylinder engine sequence.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('911', '', '44', '  c. Explain the purpose of the spark gap.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('912', '', '45', '  d. Demonstrate how to change the spark plugs in any internal combustion engine (lawn mower, dirt bike, motorcycle).', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('913', '', '46', '  e. Demonstrate how to safely connect jumper cables to your car battery.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('914', '', '47', '9. Drive Train. Do the following:', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('915', '', '48', '  a. Diagram the drive train and explain the different parts.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('916', '', '49', '  b. Explain the difference between automatic and standard transmissions.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('917', '', '50', '  c. Explain the types of automatic transmission fluid.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('918', '', '51', '  d. Explain the types of lubricants used in a standard transmission and in the differential.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('919', '', '52', '  e. Explain the difference between front-wheel, rear- wheel, and four-wheel drive.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('920', '', '53', '10. Brake System. Do the following:', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('921', '', '54', '  1. Explain the brake system (including anti-lock systems) and how it operates.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('922', '', '55', '  2. Explain the differences between disc and drum systems.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('923', '', '56', '  3. Demonstrate how to check the condition of a vehicle\'s brake system. After checking make recommendations for repairs (if necessary).', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('924', '', '57', '11. Do two of the following:', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('925', '', '58', '  1. Determine the value of three different vehicles you are interested in purchasing. One must be new and one must be used; the third vehicle can be new or used. For each vehicle, find out the requirements and cost of automobile insurance to include basic liability and options for collision, comprehensive, towing, and rental car. Using the three vehicles you chose and with your merit badge counselor\'s assistance, complete the operation/maintenance chart provided in the merit badge pamphlet. Use this information to determine the operating cost per mile for each vehicle, and discuss what you learn with your counselor.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('926', '', '59', '  2. Choose a car cleaner and wax product for a vehicle you want to clean. Explain clear-coat paint and the precautions necessary for care. Clean the vehicle, both inside and out, and wax the exterior. Use a vinyl and rubber protectant (on vinyl tops, rubber door seals, sidewalls, etc.) and explain the importance of the protectant.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('927', '', '60', '  3. Locate the manufacturer\'s jack Use the jack to demonstrate how to engage the jack correctly on the vehicle, then change a tire correctly.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('928', '', '61', '  4. Perform an oil filter and oil change on a vehicle. Explain how to properly dispose of the used oil and filter.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('929', '', '62', '12. Find out about three career opportunities in the automotive industry. Pick one and find out about the education, training, and experience required for this profession. Discuss this with your counselor, and explain why this profession might interest you.', '34', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('930', '', '1', '1.  Do the following:', '35', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('931', '', '2', '  a. Define \'aircraft.\' Describe some kinds and uses of aircraft today. Explain the operation of piston, turboprop, and jet engines. ', '35', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('932', '', '3', '  b. Point out on a model airplane the forces that act on an airplane in flight. ', '35', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('933', '', '4', '  c. Explain how an airfoil generates lift, how the primary control surfaces (ailerons, elevators, and rudder) affect the airplane\'s attitude, and how a propeller produces thrust. ', '35', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('934', '', '5', '  d. Demonstrate how the control surfaces of an airplane are used for takeoff, straight climb, level turn, climbing turn, descending turn, straight descent, and landing. ', '35', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('935', '', '6', '  e. Explain the following: the recreational pilot and the private pilot certificates; the instrument rating. ', '35', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('936', '', '7', '2. Do TWO of the following:', '35', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('937', '', '8', '  a. Take a flight in an aircraft, with your parent\'s permission. Record the date, place, type of aircraft, and duration of flight, and report on your impressions of the flight. ', '35', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('938', '', '9', '  b. Under supervision, perform a preflight inspection of a light airplane. ', '35', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('939', '', '10', '  c. Obtain and learn how to read an aeronautical chart. Measure a true course on the chart. Correct it for magnetic variation, compass deviation, and wind drift. Arrive at a compass heading. ', '35', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('940', '', '11', '  d. Using one of many flight simulator software packages available for computers. fly the course and heading you established in requirement 2c or another course you have plotted. ', '35', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('941', '', '12', '  e. On a map, mark a route for an imaginary airline trip to at least three different locations. Start from the commercial airport nearest your home. From timetables (obtained from agents or online from a computer, with your parent\'s permission), decide when you will get to and leave from all connecting points. Create an aviation flight plan and itinerary for each destination. ', '35', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('942', '', '13', '  f. Explain the purposes and functions of the various instruments found in a typical single-engine aircraft: attitude indicator, heading indicator, altimeter, airspeed indicator, turn and bank indicator, vertical speed indicator, compass, navigation (GPS and VOR) and communication radios, tachometer, oil pressure gauge, and oil temperature gauge. ', '35', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('943', '', '14', '  g. Create an original poster of an aircraft instrument panel. Include and identify the instruments and radios discussed in requirement 2f. ', '35', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('944', '', '15', '3. Do ONE of the following:', '35', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('945', '', '16', '  a. Build and fly a fuel-driven or battery powered electric model airplane. Describe safety rules for building and flying model airplanes Tell safety rules for use of glue, paint, dope, plastics, fuel, and battery pack. ', '35', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('946', '', '17', '  b. Build a model FPG-9. Get others in your troop or patrol to make their own model, then organize a competition to test the precision of flight and landing of the models. ', '35', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('947', '', '18', '4. Do ONE of the following:', '35', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('948', '', '19', '  a. Visit an airport. After the visit, report on how the facilities are used, how runways are numbered, and how runways are determined to be \'active.\' ', '35', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('949', '', '20', '  b. Visit a Federal Aviation Administration facility control tower, terminal radar control facility, air route traffic control center, flight service station, or Flight Standards District Office. (Phone directory listings are under U.S. Government Offices, Transportation Department, Federal Aviation Administration. Call in advance.) Report on the operation and your impressions of the facility. ', '35', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('950', '', '21', '  c. Visit an aviation museum or attend an air show. Report on your impressions of the museum or show. ', '35', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('951', '', '22', '5. Find out about three career opportunities in aviation. Pick one and find out the education, training, and experience required for this profession. Discuss this with your counselor, and explain why this profession might interest you. ', '35', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('952', '', '1', '1.  Discuss the prevention of and treatment for the health concerns that could occur while backpacking, including hypothermia, heat reactions, frostbite, dehydration, insect stings, tick bites, snakebite, and blisters.', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('953', '', '2', '2. Do the following:', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('954', '', '3', '  a. List 10 items that are essential to be carried on any backpacking trek and explain why each item is necessary. ', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('955', '', '4', '  b. Describe 10 ways you can limit the weight and bulk to be carried in your pack without jeopardizing your health or safety. ', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('956', '', '5', '3. Do the following:', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('957', '', '6', '  a. Define limits on the number of backpackers appropriate for a trek crew. ', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('958', '', '7', '  b. Describe how a trek crew should be organized. ', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('959', '', '8', '  c. Tell how you would minimize risk on a backpacking trek. ', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('960', '', '9', '4. Do the following:', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('961', '', '10', '  a. Describe the importance of using Leave No Trace principles while backpacking, and at least five ways you can lessen the crew\'s impact on the environment. ', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('962', '', '11', '  b. Describe proper methods of handling human and other wastes while on a backpacking trek. Describe the importance of and means to assure personal cleanliness while on a backpacking trek. ', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('963', '', '12', '  c. Tell what factors are important in choosing a campsite. ', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('964', '', '13', '5. Do the following:', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('965', '', '14', '  a. Demonstrate two ways to treat water and tell why water treatment is essential. ', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('966', '', '15', '  b. Explain to your counselor the importance of staying well hydrated during a trek. ', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('967', '', '16', '6. Do the following:', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('968', '', '17', '  a. Demonstrate that you can read topographic maps. ', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('969', '', '18', '  b. While on a trek, use a map and compass to establish your position on the ground at least three times at three different places, OR use a GPS receiver to establish your position on a topographic map and on the ground at least three times at three different places. ', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('970', '', '19', '  c. Explain how to stay found, and what to do if you get lost. ', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('971', '', '20', '7. Tell how to prepare properly for and deal with inclement weather.', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('972', '', '21', '8. Do the following:', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('973', '', '22', '  a. Explain the advantages and disadvantages of three different types of backpacking stoves using at least three different types of fuel. ', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('974', '', '23', '  b. Demonstrate that you know how to operate a backpacking stove safely and to handle liquid fuel safely. ', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('975', '', '24', '  c. Prepare at least three meals using a stove and fuel you can carry in a backpack. ', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('976', '', '25', '  d. Demonstrate that you know how to keep cooking and eating gear clean and sanitary and that you practice proper methods for food storage while on a backpacking trek. ', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('977', '', '26', '9. Do the following:', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('978', '', '27', '  a. Write a plan for a patrol backpacking hike that includes a time control plan. ', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('979', '', '28', '  b. Show that you know how to properly pack your personal gear and your share of the crew\'s gear and food. ', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('980', '', '29', '  c. Show you can properly shoulder your pack and adjust it for proper wear. ', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('981', '', '30', '  d. Conduct a prehike inspection of the patrol and its equipment. ', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('982', '', '31', '  e. While carrying your pack, complete a hike of at least 2 miles. ', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('983', '', '32', '10. Using Leave No Trace principles, participate in at least three backpacking treks of at least three days each and at least 15 miles each, and using at least two different campsites on each trek. Carry everything you will need throughout the trek.', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('984', '', '33', '11. Do the following:', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('985', '', '34', '  a. Write a plan for a backpacking trek of at least five days using at least three different campsites and covering at least 30 miles. Your plan must include a description of and route to the trek area, a schedule (including a daily schedule), a list of food and equipment needs, a safety and emergency plan, and a budget. ', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('986', '', '35', '  b. Using Leave No Trace principles, take the trek planned and, while on the trek, complete at least one service project approved by your merit badge counselor. ', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('987', '', '36', '  c. Keep a daily journal during the trek that includes a day-by-day description of you activities, including notes about what worked well and thoughts about improvements that could be made for the next trek. ', '36', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('988', '', '1', '1. Describe precautions you should take to safely use basketry tools and materials.', '37', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('989', '', '2', '2. Do the following:', '37', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('990', '', '3', '  a. Show your counselor that you are able to identify each of the following types of baskets: plaited, coiled, ribbed, and wicker. ', '37', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('991', '', '4', '  b. Describe three different types of weaves to your counselor. ', '37', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('992', '', '5', '3. Plan and weave each of the following projects:', '37', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('993', '', '6', '  a. a square basket', '37', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('994', '', '7', '  b. a round basket', '37', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('995', '', '8', '  c. a campstool seat', '37', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('996', '', '1', '1. Explain the need for bird study and why birds are useful indicators of the quality of the environment.', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('997', '', '2', '2. Show that you are familiar with the terms used to describe birds by sketching or tracing a perched bird and then labeling 15 different parts of the bird. Sketch or trace an extended wing and label types of wing feathers.', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('998', '', '3', '3. Demonstrate that you know how to properly use and care for binoculars.', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('999', '', '4', '  a. Explain what the specification numbers on the binoculars mean. ', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1000', '', '5', '  b. Show how to adjust the eyepiece and how to focus for proper viewing. ', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1001', '', '6', '  c. Show how to properly care for and clean the lenses. ', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1002', '', '7', '4. Demonstrate that you know how to use a bird field guide. Show your counselor that you are able to understand a range map by locating in the book and pointing out the wintering range, the breeding range, and/or the year-round range of one species of each of the following types of birds:', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1003', '', '8', '  a. Seabird ', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1004', '', '9', '  b. Plover ', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1005', '', '10', '  c. Falcon or hawk ', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1006', '', '11', '  d. Warbler or vireo ', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1007', '', '12', '  e. Heron or egret ', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1008', '', '13', '  f. Sparrow ', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1009', '', '14', '  g. Nonnative bird (introduced to North America from a foreign country since 1800) ', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1010', '', '15', '5. Observe and be able to identify at least 20 species of wild birds. Prepare a field notebook, making a separate entry for each species, and record the following information from your field observations and other references.', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1011', '', '16', '  a. Note the date and time. ', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1012', '', '17', '  b. Note the location and habitat. ', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1013', '', '18', '  c. Describe the bird\'s main feeding habitat and list two types of food that the bird is likely to eat. ', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1014', '', '19', '  d. Note whether the bird is a migrant or a summer, winter, or year-round resident of your area. ', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1015', '', '20', '6. Explain the function of a bird\'s song. Be able to identify five of the 20 species in your field notebook by song or call alone. For each of these five species enter a description of the song or call, and note the behavior of the bird making the sound. Note why you think the bird was making the call or song that you heard.', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1016', '', '21', '7. Do ONE of the following:', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1017', '', '22', '  a. Go on a field trip with a local club or with others who are knowledgeable about birds in your area.', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1018', '', '23', '    1. Keep a list or fill out a checklist of all the birds your group observed during the field trip. ', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1019', '', '24', '    2. Tell your counselor which birds your group saw and why some species were common and some were present in small numbers. ', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1020', '', '25', '    3. Tell your counselor what makes the area you visited good for finding birds. ', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1021', '', '26', '  b. By using a public library or contacting the National Audubon Society, find the name and location of the Christmas Bird Count nearest your home and obtain the results of a recent count.', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1022', '', '27', '    1. Explain what kinds of information are collected during the annual event. ', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1023', '', '28', '    2. Tell your counselor which species are most common, and explain why these birds are abundant. ', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1024', '', '29', '    3. Tell your counselor which species are uncommon, and explain why these were present in small numbers. If the number of birds of these species is decreasing, explain why, and what, if anything, could be done to reverse their decline. ', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1025', '', '30', '8. Do ONE of the following. For the option you choose, describe what birds you hope to attract, and why.', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1026', '', '31', '  a. Build a bird feeder and put it in an appropriate place in your yard or another location. ', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1027', '', '32', '  b. Build a birdbath and put it in an appropriate place. ', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1028', '', '33', '  c. Build a backyard sanctuary for birds by planting trees and shrubs for food and cover. ', '38', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1029', '', '1', '1. Give a brief history of the bugle.', '39', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1030', '', '2', '2. Do the following:', '39', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1031', '', '3', '  a. Explain and demonstrate how the bugle makes sound, and explain how the bugle is related to other brass wind instruments. ', '39', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1032', '', '4', '  b. Compose a bugle call for your troop or patrol to signal a common group activity, such as assembling for mealtime or striking a campsite. ', '39', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1033', '', '5', '3. Sound the following bugle calls: \'First Call,\' \'Reveille,\' \'Assembly,\' \'Mess,\' \'Drill,\' \'Fatigue,\' \'Officers,\' \'Recall,\' \'Church,\' \'Swimming,\' \'Fire,\' \'Retreat,\' \'To the Colors,\' \'Call to Quarters,\' and \'Taps.\'', '39', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1034', '', '6', '4. Explain when each of the calls in requirement 3 is used.', '39', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1035', '', '7', '5. Explain how to care for, clean, and maintain a bugle.', '39', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1036', '', '8', '6. Serve as bugler in your troop for three months. * ', '39', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1037', '', '3', '  b. Review prevention, symptoms, and first-aid treatment for the following injuries or illnesses that could occur while canoeing: blisters, cold-water shock and hypothermia, dehydration, heat-related illnesses, sunburn, sprains, and strains.', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1038', '', '60', '(No Longer Required) Do the following:', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1039', '', '61', ' (No Longer Required) a. Identify the conditions that must exist before performing CPR on a person. Explain how such conditions are recognized. ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1040', '', '62', ' (No Longer Required)  b. Demonstrate the proper technique for performing CPR using a training device approved by your counselor. ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1041', '', '5', '2. Before doing the following requirements, successfully complete the BSA swimmer test: Jump feetfirst into water over the head in depth. Level off and swim 75 yards in a strong manner using one or more of the following strokes: sidestroke, breaststroke, trudgen, or crawl; then swim 25 yards using an easy, resting backstroke. The 100 yards must be completed in one swim without stops and must include at least one sharp turn. After completing the swim, rest by floating.', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1042', '', '6', '3. Do the following:', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1043', '', '4', '  c. Discuss the BSA Safety Afloat policy. Tell how it applies to canoeing activities. ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1044', '', '68', '  b. The most common weather and water-related hazards encountered while canoeing and how to deal safely with each one. ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1045', '', '10', '4. Do the following:', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1046', '', '7', '  a. Name and point out the major parts of a canoe. ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1047', '', '8', '  b. Describe how the length and shape of a canoe affect its performance. ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1048', '', '9', '  c. Discuss the advantages and disadvantages of the different materials used to make canoes. ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1049', '', '11', ' a. Name and point out the parts of a paddle. Explain the difference between a straight and bent-shaft paddle and when each is best used. ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1050', '', '12', '  b. Demonstrate how to correctly size a paddle for a paddler in a sitting position and a kneeling position. ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1051', '', '14', '  a. Discuss with your counselor the characteristics of life jackets most appropriate for canoeing and tell why a life jacket must always be worn while paddling. ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1052', '', '15', '  b. Demonstrate how to select and properly fit the correct size life jacket.', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1053', '', '16', '6. Discuss with your counselor the general care and maintenance of canoes, paddles, and other canoeing equipment. ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1054', '', '18', ' a. Discuss what personal and group equipment would be appropriate for a canoe camping trip. Describe how personal and group equipment can be packed and protected from water. ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1055', '', '19', '  b. Using the containers and packs from requirement 7a, demonstrate how to load and secure the containers and other equipment in the canoe. ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1056', '', '20', '  c. Using appropriate knots, including a truckerâ€™s hitch, tautline hitch, and bowline, demonstrate how to secure a canoe to a vehicle or a trailer, or if these are not available, a rack on land. ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1057', '', '21', '8. With a companion, use a properly equipped canoe to demonstrate the following: ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1058', '', '22', '  a. Safely carry and launch the canoe from a dock or shore (both, if possible). ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1059', '', '23', '  b. Safely land the canoe on a dock or shore (both, if possible) and return it to its proper storage location. ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1060', '', '24', '  c. Demonstrate kneeling and sitting positions in a canoe and explain the proper use for each position. ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1061', '', '25', '  d. Change places while afloat in the canoe. ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1062', '', '27', '  a. In deep water, exit the canoe and get back in without capsizing. ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1063', '', '28', '  b. Safely perform a controlled capsize of the canoe and demonstrate how staying with a capsized canoe will support both paddlers. ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1064', '', '29', '  c. Swim, tow, or push a swamped canoe 50 feet to shallow water. In the shallow water, empty the swamped canoe and reenter it.', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1065', '', '30', '  d. In deep water, rescue a swamped canoe and its paddlers by emptying the swamped canoe and helping the paddlers safely reenter their boat without capsizing.', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1066', '', '31', '10. With a companion, use a properly equipped canoe to demonstrate the following paddling strokes as both a bow and stern paddler:', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1067', '', '32', '  a. Forward stroke ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1068', '', '33', '  b. Backstroke ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1069', '', '34', '  c. Draw ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1070', '', '35', '  d. Pushaway ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1071', '', '36', '  e. Forward sweep ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1072', '', '37', '  f. Reverse sweep\n     For stern paddling only: ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1073', '', '38', '  g. J-stroke ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1074', '', '40', '11. Using the strokes in requirement 10, and in an order determined by your counselor, use a properly equipped canoe to demonstrate the following tandem maneuvers while paddling on opposite sides and without changing sides. Each paddler must demonstrate these maneuvers in both the bow and stern and on opposite paddling sides:\r\n\r\n', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1075', '', '41', '  a. Pivot or spin the canoe in either direction. ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1076', '', '42', '  b. Move the canoe sideways or abeam in either direction. ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1077', '', '43', '  c. Stop the canoe. ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1078', '', '44', '  d. Move the canoe in a straight line for 50 yards. ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1079', '', '45', '12. Use a properly equipped canoe to demonstrate solo canoe handling: ', '40', '');
INSERT INTO `RequirementConfig` VALUES ('1080', '', '46', '  a. Launch from shore or a pier (both, if possible). ', '40', '');
